docs.lead_paragraph: Republicans talk about their commitment to the poor. So why haven’t we heard the party’s candidates talk about the crisis in Flint, Mich.?
docs.abstract: Op-Ed article by speechwriter Matt Latimer criticizes Republicans for neglecting recent toxic water crisis in his hometown of Flint, Mich; argues conservatives squandered chance to use wrenching decline of city, once headquarters of General Motors, to prove their commitment to African-Americans and finding solutions to urban poverty.

docs.abstract: Those canvassing for Hillary Clinton in Iowa face frigid temperatures, rejection, indecision and outright hostility as they carry out thankless job; door-to-door canvassing remains, nevertheless, one of most effective ways to turn out vote.
